oracle.apps.fnd.applcore.extensions.migration
Class FndExtensionApplicationMigrator

java.lang.Object
  oracle.apps.fnd.applcore.extensions.migration.FndExtensionApplicationMigrator
All Implemented Interfaces:
oracle.adf.share.customizationset.CSMigrator, oracle.adf.share.customizationset.CSMigratorExtension
public class FndExtensionApplicationMigrator
extends java.lang.Object
implements oracle.adf.share.customizationset.CSMigrator, oracle.adf.share.customizationset.CSMigratorExtension

This class is EXT sub-module in ADF CSM module. This participates while exporting/importing horizontal extension. 1. Export - While exporting horizontal extension in partner development POD, MDS sub module of ADF module takes care of exporting MDS contents of the horizontal extension. This ADF-EXT sub module takes care exporting metadata file required for migrating OPSS policies, menu entries.. This sub module will produce a jar file CS_ADF_EXT_.jar in CSLoc passed by CSM Orchestrator. An exported horizontal extension with short name 'ICM' will be as shown below CS_13911049392988.jar - Exported Horizontal Extension | --> ADF - Directory which contains the file produced by ADF module | --> CS_ADF_13911049383988.jar - File produced by ADF module by consolidating all the files produced its sub modules. | --> CS_ADF_MDS_13911049383988.jar - File produced by MDS sub module of the ADF module this contains all the MDS contents of the horizontal extension. | --> CS_ADF_EXT_13911049383988.jar - File produced by this class. CS_ADF_MDS_13911049383988.jar - This contains all the documents (base & cust) in the namespace "/oracle/apps/extensions/ICM" CS_ADF_EXT_13911049383988.jar - This contains only horizontal extension metadata file i.e "extension.xml" in the horizontal extension namespace. 2. Backup - While installing horizontal extension in a POD, backup will be invoked before import to restore the system state when install fails. MDS sub module takes care of documents in MDS by creating a label. EXT sub module (i.e this class) will simply make a copy of the CS_ADF_EXT_13911049383988.jar to create backup jar CS_ADF_EXT_BACKUP.jar. 3. Import - 4. Restore-
